  "text": "Django's CSRF protection is implemented across several key files in the django/django repository. The main middleware class CsrfViewMiddleware (django/middleware/csrf.py:165) validates CSRF tokens on POST requests through its process_view method. When validating tokens, the middleware calls _check_token (line 349) which retrieves the CSRF secret and validates the incoming token. The actual token comparison happens in _does_token_match (line 143) which uses constant_time_compare from django/utils/crypto.py (line 65) to prevent timing attacks. The constant_time_compare function wraps Python's secrets.compare_digest(), ensuring that token comparison takes constant time regardless of where the mismatch occurs, eliminating timing-based attack vectors. The csrf_protect decorator (django/views/decorators/csrf.py:7) applies the same CsrfViewMiddleware protection to individual views by using decorator_from_middleware. Token generation and masking is handled by _mask_cipher_secret (line 59) and _unmask_cipher_token (line 71), which use a one-time pad cipher to mask the CSRF secret. The get_token function (line 96) returns a masked token for form submissions. Additional security decorators include csrf_exempt (line 50) for exempting views, requires_csrf_token (line 22) for ensuring token availability without enforcement, and ensure_csrf_cookie (line 42) for guaranteeing CSRF cookie presence. Security configuration checks are implemented in django/core/checks/security/csrf.py to ensure proper CSRF middleware configuration and secure cookie settings. The csrf_failure view (django/views/csrf.py:22) handles rendering error responses when CSRF validation fails."
}

